co2cargo: A wrapper around cargo that supports CO2 language features.

Usage: co2cargo <subcommand> [args...]

CO2 Specific Commands:
    init        Initialize a new co2 project in an existing directory.
                Creates src/main.co2 and adds #![language(co2)] to src/main.rs.

Common Cargo Commands (forwarded with RUSTC=co2rustc):
    build, b    Compile the current package
    check, c    Analyze the current package and report errors
    doc         Build this package's documentation
    run, r      Run a binary or example of the local package
    test, t     Run the tests
    add         Add dependencies to a manifest file
    miri        Run the project under miri via cargo-miri.
                Requires cargo-miri to be installed.

All other cargo commands are supported and forwarded to cargo.
